attributes.Long form description: The student disassembles the table. He first removes the tabletop, unscrews the top hex socket head of each leg, detaches the tabletop, then disassembles the shelf of the table, unscrews all the hex socket heads, and finally puts all the parts separately.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the table top.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: Student should not drop the hex socket head.
The hex socket head hasn't  been completely loosened yet.
The student later decides to use the Allen key instead of his hands.
Student should not drop the Allen key.
Student should not drop the hex socket head.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles some of the hex socket heads attached to the lower tray to disassemble the legs more easily.
The student disassembles the first leg of the table.
The student disassembles the second leg of the furniture.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student shouldn't drop the hex_socket_head.

attributes.Action sentence: The student  disassembles the third leg of the furniture.
The student disassembles the rest of the furniture.
